1 by the applicable State entity, a drug or alcohol treatment counseling
2 program, as appropriate."
3
4 PART II. CONFORMING CHANGES
5 SECTION 2. The following statutes are repealed:
6 (1) G.S. 20-9(b1).
7 (2) G.S. 20-13.2(c1).
8 (3) G.S. 115C-12(28).
9 (4) G.S. 115C-150.12C(19).
10 (5) G.S. 115C-218.70.
11 (6) G.S. 115C-238.66(8).
12 (7) G.S. 115C-288(k).
13 (8) G.S. 115C-566.
14
15 PART III. EFFECTIVE DATE
16 SECTION 3. This act becomes effective October 1, 2025, and applies to permit or
17 provisional license applications submitted on or after that date.
